<PageLayout title="AI Auto-Trading Experiment" description="An experiment building and running an automated trading system with AI and ₩5M. No code written by hand — just rules, an AI assistant, and real capital on the line.">
  <div class="project-detail">
    <a href="/en/projects" class="back-link">← Projects</a>

    <div class="project-header">
      <span class="project-status status-active">Active</span>
      <h1>AI Auto-Trading Experiment</h1>
      <p class="project-meta">Current version: <strong>v1.1</strong> · Last updated: <strong>2026-04-10</strong></p>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>An experiment building and running an automated trading system with AI and ₩5M. No guarantees of success. Learning while building.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Why I Started</h2>
      <p>34 years as a semiconductor engineer. Systems thinking — designing, verifying, iterating — is wired into how I work. I wanted to apply that same mindset to financial automation.</p>
      <p>The goal isn't profit. It's the experience of building a system where AI operates real capital — and doing it myself.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>System Architecture</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>A <strong>rule engine</strong> based on moving averages and RSI makes all trading decisions</li>
        <li>AI assists with analysis and reports — it does not decide</li>
        <li>Real-time trade alerts via Telegram</li>
        <li>2-week paper trading validation before switching to a live account</li>
        <li>Runs as a long-running scheduler process; after any code change, the process is restarted per SOP and the change is visually confirmed.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Current Position</h2>
      <p><strong>MVP stabilization complete → entering paper trading live verification</strong></p>
      <p>The goal shifted from building a system that simply runs to building a structure that can actually be operated. This update was that turning point.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>2026.04.10 Update — Production-Grade Structural Overhaul Complete</h2>
      <p>This wasn't patching a few lines of code. It was building the infrastructure needed to run an automated trading system reliably. Direction and situation assessment handled by Meta-Chulbuji; actual code analysis, fixes, and verification handled by a specialized dev AI and Claude Code. 11 items overhauled in two hours yesterday evening.</p>

      <h3>✅ Stability Fixes</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Cash balance field replacement</td><td>Wrong field reference → replaced with correct field</td></tr>
          <tr><td>API retry logic</td><td>Added retry structure on call failure</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Duplicate buy prevention</td><td>Block duplicate buys on the same ticker</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Duplicate process prevention</td><td>Prevent multiple scheduler instances from running</td></tr>
          <tr><td>hold_days bug fix</td><td>Fixed error in position holding day calculation</td></tr>
          <tr><td>IS_PAPER safety guard</td><td>Prevent paper/live mode cross-contamination</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>✅ Strategy Refinements</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>RSI Wilder method</td><td>Previous method → switched to Wilder smoothing</td></tr>
          <tr><td>RSI range adjustment</td><td>Adjusted to 40–65</td></tr>
          <tr><td>MA20 deviation cap</td><td>Added condition: within 5% of MA20</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Investment allocation expanded</td><td>20%, up to ₩1,000,000 per position</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Trailing stop introduced</td><td>First implementation of profit-zone protection</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>✅ Operations Structure</h3>
      <table class="update-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Buy scan structure</td><td>1× pre-market + 4× intraday</td></tr>
          <tr><td>DRY RUN / LIVE separation</td><td>Clearly distinguished in logs and Telegram</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Post-market summary</td><td>Automatic daily operations summary</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Verification checkpoint</td><td>Monday first-run checklist defined</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>How Operations Work Now</h2>
      <p>This update established the collaboration structure for the project going forward.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>With Meta-Chulbuji</strong> — direction, situation assessment, strategy prioritization</li>
        <li><strong>With specialized dev AI</strong> — code analysis, fixes, verification, implementation</li>
      </ul>
      <p>From chasing each bug myself to focusing on direction and judgment. Dividing the roles changed the pace.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Next Milestone</h2>
      <p><strong>2026.04.14 (Mon) — First paper trading live verification</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>First confirmation of how the system behaves in a real market session</li>
        <li>Live validation of buy scan structure, trailing stop, and log separation</li>
        <li>Any unexpected behavior logged immediately and addressed</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Roadmap</h2>
      <p>The overhaul is done — but the system isn't finished. Next steps depend on what the first live run reveals.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Review adding volume surge condition</li>
        <li>Migrate ticker universe to .env</li>
        <li>Design sector diversification structure</li>
        <li>Score-based buy prioritization</li>
        <li>Establish SOP for live account switchover</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Update History</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>2026-04-10</strong> — Production-grade structural overhaul: cash balance field fix / API retry logic / duplicate buy & process prevention / hold_days bug fix / IS_PAPER safety guard / RSI Wilder method / RSI range 40–65 / MA20 deviation 5% cap / allocation 20% up to ₩1M / trailing stop introduced / operations collaboration structure redesigned</li>
        <li><strong>2026-04-09</strong> — Python module cache issue identified — confirmed in live operation that code changes are not reflected without restarting the scheduler. Added diagnostic logs to is_market_ok() / MA60 fallback to close > MA20 for paper trading environment applied / same fallback applied to check_buy_signal() / BUY reason string format error fixed / DRY_RUN buy cycle restored / scheduler restart SOP document created</li>
        <li><strong>v1.1</strong> · 2026-04-08 — Dual regime filter / ₩10B volume filter / IMMEDIATE·NEXT_OPEN sell branching / same-day rebuy block / log system overhaul</li>
        <li><strong>v1.0</strong> · 2026-04-07 — KIS API, rule engine, Telegram alerts, scheduler MVP complete</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Related Logs</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/en/log/2026-04-10-auto-trading-11-fixes">KIS Auto-Trading — Two Hours, 11 Items Fixed</a> (2026-04-10 Log)</li>
        <li><a href="/en/insight/insight-011">I Didn't Have AI Fix the Code — I Redesigned the Structure</a> (2026-04-10 Insight)</li>
        <li><a href="/en/log/2026-04-09-auto-trading-module-cache">Auto-Trading — Module Cache Issue Identified & Buy Cycle Restored</a> (2026-04-09 Log)</li>
        <li><a href="/en/insight/insight-010">I Fixed the Code. Why Didn't the System Change?</a> (2026-04-09 Insight)</li>
        <li><a href="/en/log/2026-04-08-auto-trading-v11">Auto-Trading v1.1 Setup & First Run Standby Log</a> (2026-04-08)</li>
        <li><a href="/en/log/stock-auto-trade-mvp-complete">Auto-Trading MVP Complete Log</a> (2026-04-07)</li>
